sentences: Aaron Yan (traditional Chinese: 炎亞綸; simplified Chinese: 炎亚纶, born Wu Keng-lin on 20 November 1985) is a Taiwanese actor and singer.
=== 1985–2005: Early life and career beginnings ===
section: == Life and career == | === 1985–2005: Early life and career beginnings ===

sentences: Yan was born as Wu Keng-lin in Taipei, Taiwan on 20 November 1985.
section: == Life and career == | === 1985–2005: Early life and career beginnings ===

sentences: In 2004, Yan posted some of his pictures on a public blog and was scouted by Taiwanese management company, Comic Productions.
section: == Life and career == | === 1985–2005: Early life and career beginnings ===

sentences: In August 2004, he made his acting debut in Taiwanese drama, I Love My Wife.
section: == Life and career == | === 1985–2005: Early life and career beginnings ===

sentences: In 2005, after signing with Comic Productions and HIM International Music, Yan starred in Taiwanese dramas, It Started with a Kiss and KO One.
section: == Life and career == | === 1985–2005: Early life and career beginnings ===

sentences: In December 2005, he formed a boy band named Fahrenheit with three other Taiwanese artists: Wu Chun, Jiro Wang, and Calvin Chen.
In September 2006, Fahrenheit released their eponymous debut studio album, Fahrenheit, and they won a Hito Music Award for Best Boy Band.
In 2007, Yan reprised his roles in the sequels The X-Family and They Kiss Again.
In November 2008, Yan played his first leading role in Taiwanese suspense drama, Mysterious Incredible Terminator.
=== 2011–present:
In March 2011, Yan released his debut extended play, The Next Me.
In May 2012, Yan starred in Taiwanese musical drama, Alice in Wonder City.
In October 2012, he released his debut studio album, The Moment.
In June 2013, Yan starred in Taiwanese romantic comedy drama, Just You.
In February 2014, Yan starred in Taiwanese metropolitan romance drama, Fall in Love with Me.
In May 2014, he released his second extended play, Drama.
In June 2014, he released his third extended play, Cut.
In March 2015, Yan debuted in Japan with the single titled, "Moisturizing".
In September 2015, he released his second Japanese single, "Gelato".
In March 2016, Yan starred in Taiwanese workplace romance drama, Refresh Man.
In June 2016, Yan released his third Japanese single "Monochrome Dandy".
In 2017, Yan was cast in the Chinese romance drama, Memories of Love.
In 2018, Yan released his forth extended play Where I Belong.
In 2019, Yan starred as the male lead in period suspense drama Please Give Me a Pair of Wings.
On 7 May 2020, Yan launched his Taiwan mazesoba brand, Yan's Collection.
On 25 Dec 2020, Yan released sixth extended play "Metropolis" which comprises self-composed songs.
When he was very young, he and his family moved to Connecticut, United States, where he lived for five years, and then moved back to Taiwan.

sentences: He also starred in Love Buffet and Gloomy Salad Days.

In October 2012, he released his debut studio album, The Moment.
In February 2014, Yan starred in Taiwanese metropolitan romance drama, Fall in Love with Me.
The same year Yan released his fifth extended play Dear Monster which includes the single "Sleeping Titan".
The same year, he co-starred in the romance comedy drama Kiss Love, and Taste.
